==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bluntness
<hw>Blunt"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Want of edge or
point; dullness; obtuseness; lack of sharpness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The multitude of elements and <qex>bluntness</qex> of angles.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Abruptness of address; rude plainness.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Bluntness</xex> of speech.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blunt-witted</ent>⟦br⟧
